txt.en: 'Our conflict is not with your pathetic Vale, yet you persist, interfering with my affairs.'
'That is why I shall show you no mercy in the pain I cause you!'
'Neither are we.'
'I see fear in your eyes.'
'How are you defeating our best warriors?!'
'You will see defeat on this day!'
'Attack the intruders!'
'You'll not defeat me this time! I shall take to the west!'
'I shall see this confrontation until the end!'
'I'll defeat you myself!'
'You, [placeholder], have foiled our plans one too many times.'
'Pathetic!'
'Shall we destroy them Drugât?'
'You can not defeat me!'
'Why do you persist?!'
'Quickly my friend, prepare to defend yourself!'
'You've bested me one too many times! I shall depart before you defeat me again!'
'Why do the living always interfere?'
'I did not come here to fight.'
'You heard Drugât. Leave pests! We shall depart this Vale soon.'
'Farewell.'
'Men, we leave this place and return to the mountain!'
'Quiet Nerzus.'
'You are not welcome here. I remember you.'
'I recommend you leave as I am not interested in your land.'
'Puny filth!'
'I'll smash you into tiny pieces!'
'Stand still!'
'For Drugât!'
'Quickly, this way!'
'This hall looks ancient.'
'Brace youself! This troll taunts us!'
'There must be a way to unlock the gate.'
'Onward!'
'Let our blades do the talking.'
'We are not here to negotiate, vile spectres!'
'Silence Nerzus.'
'This cave is lined with the ruins of some ancient path.'
'A great power has called us away from our land.'
'The doors to the inner hall wince open as the inner hall gasps for breath.'
'It is a slow journey as we dead are not accustomed to travel.'
'However, the darkened skies ease the way for my people.'
